Description: Lip and wall sherd (mended from three fragments) of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery rosette bowl; interior glazed with added white band on wall; exterior: dot-rosette, black line at top of lip; inscription cut over rosette.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.848)
